  "prompt": "What is the meaning of ULK in BMW?",
  "response": "In the context of BMW, \"ULK\" is an abbreviation for \"Untere Luftklappe,\" which translates from German to \"lower air flap\" in English. These flaps are part of the vehicle's aerodynamic and cooling systems, helping to manage airflow and optimize engine cooling and aerodynamic efficiency. By adjusting the position of these flaps, the vehicle can improve fuel economy and reduce drag when cooling demands are low.",
